Data Type : data specified the type of data which the variable is going to store

Primitive Data Types

8 types of primitive datatypes


1 byte = 8 bits

byte  :  1 byte - range is : -128 to 127 : whole numbers
short :  2 byte - range is : -32,768 to 32,767 : whole numbers
int   :  4 byte - range is : 2 cr : : whole numbers
long  :  8 byte - range is : 4 cr : : whole numbers
float :  4 byte - range is : 6 to 7 decmial places   : : fractional/decimal numbers  ex : 12.123456
double: 8 byte - range is : 15 decimal places   : : fractional/decimal numbers  ex : 12.123456
char  :   2 bytes - only single charecters ex : a,b,c,d .... etc 
boolean : 1 bit - true or false

 
Non Primitive Data Types

these are created by the programmer - 

Strings, Arrays, classes etc...


